  "texts": [
    "We will slightly reformulate this description in order to relate it to Stokes local systems.",
    "As before, we always consider the Riemann sphere Σ = P 1 (C) and an irregular class Θ at ∞.",
    "Throughout this section and the rest of this article, we will make the following assumption: Assumption 4.1.",
    "There is a fixed k ∈ Q >1 such that any active circle ⟨f ⟩ of the irregular class Θ is of the form ⟨f ⟩ = ⟨az k ⟩ for some a ∈ C \\ {0}, and for any two active circles ⟨az k ⟩, ⟨bz k ⟩ ⊂ I, one has |a| = |b|.",
    "(We remark that Assumption 4.1 is not necessary in §4.1 and §5.1-5.2, unless explicitly stated.) 4.1."
